  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Specific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but typically include:\n\n1. Core Elements\n- Concealing source of illegal funds\n- Disguising financial transactions\n- Converting \"dirty\" money to appear legitimate\n\n2. Common Legal Criteria\n- Intentional financial manipulation\n- Proceeds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make funds seem legal\n\n3. Typical Stages\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (complex transactions to obscure origin)\n- Integration (reintroducing funds as seemingly legitimate)\n\n4. Jurisdictional Variations\n- US defines under Bank Secrecy Act\n- EU follows Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- International standards through FATF guidelines\n\n5. Potential Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n\nNote: Specific legal details can vary, so consulting local legal statutes is recommended for precise definitions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
